CNCP v1 23340
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#8408: props' default value does not respect typescript's inferred type when using <script> without setup",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:24:27.861228+00:00",
  "text": "props' default value does not respect typescript's inferred type when using <script> without setup\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.2.47\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nsee below\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\n<template>\r\n\t<div>\r\n\t\t<span>{{ colors$[0] }}</span>\r\n\t\t<span>{{ colors$[1] }}</span>\r\n\t\t<span>{{ colors$[2] }}</span>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</template>\r\n\r\n<script lang=\"ts\">\r\nimport { ComputedRef, computed, defineComponent, getCurrentInstance, markRaw, reactive, PropType } from 'vue';\r\n\r\ninterface Props {\r\n\tcolors?: [string, string, string];\r\n}\r\n\r\ntype VM = {\r\n\tcolors$: Props['colors'];\r\n};\r\n\r\nexport default defineComponent({\r\n\tprops: {\r\n\t\tcolors: {\r\n\t\t\ttype: Array as unknown as PropType<Props['colors']>,\r\n\t\t\tdefault: () => [1, 2, 3]\t// I can return anything as long as it is an array, even the content type doesn't match the PropType\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t},\r\n\tsetup(props) {\r\n\t\tconst vm = reactive<VM>({\r\n\t\t\tcolors$: props.colors\r\n\t\t}) as VM;\r\n\r\n\t\treturn vm;\r\n\t}\r\n});\r\n</script>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nType error will be prompted as I am not respecting the type\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nThe code still compiles...\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types"
  ],
